The Benue State government has asked the contractor, Dan-Ella Global Business Services Limited to immediately refund the sum of N54.3 million on an abandoned road project and another N26.5 million on an abandoned electricity project. LEADERSHIP Sunday gathered that the decision of the state government to terminate the two contracts was based on the fact that the contractor had abandoned the projects, contrary to the  terms of agreement it signed with the government three years ago. Governor Samuel Ortom through the Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Information and Culture, James Agbo disclosed the government’s decision after the meeting of the State Executive Council. He said the council further directed the Ministry of Rural Development and Cooperatives to award the projects to a more qualified and competent company. It was also gathered that the contractor, Dan-Ella Global Business Services Limited was handling contract for the extension of electricity from Gbajimba to Tse-Akaahena as well assistant feeder road which covers Tse-Ortom-Tse-Upev-Tse-Akaahena-Nasarawa border in Guma local government area of the state, which he later allegedly abandoned. In another development, the council has also approved the conversion of two of the state high institutions Akawe Torkula College of Advanced and Professional Studies, (ATCAPS) Makurdi to Torkula and Akperan Orshi College of Agriculture, Yandev, (AOCAY)to  Polytechnics. The governor explained that the decision of the Council to convert the two institutions to polytechnics is to enable them meet accreditation requirements set by National Board for Technical Education (NBTE).